<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/1548: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-13T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 13,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your May 11, midnight. You may inform General Crowder that Department
                                strongly advocates enactment of a law which will invalidate all
                                nominations made in this calendar year. The Department is inclined
                                to recognize only nominations made in the calendar year in which the
                                election is held and then only when such nominations have been made
                                by conventions newly constituted in the entirety within that year
                                for that special purpose.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>